name: ecstacy necklace
description:
This is a very large and mouth-droppingly fabulous OTT neckpiece which you won't be able to wear to your niece's christening, but you will able to wear it with as little as possible when you're in tropical paradise with the sound of the ocean and the scent of exotic fauna. 
You will also be able to wear it with a plain and strapless little black dress, just to show everyone that you take summer for what it is: a time of unbridled delights!

Czech and Indian glass (some vintage), 22ct gold-plated brass fittings and wire.

I dare you!!

name: julep foam necklace
description:
“There's only one very good life and that's the life you know you want and you make it yourself.” 
― Diana Vreeland

Luxury pastels webbed together in a mist of silver dreams, this necklace heart-breakingly delicate and beautiful, yet quite a strong statement of feminine elegance. 

This piece harks back to the days when I used to spend weeks and days wiring crystal beads together, its something I probably don't want to do anymore! But couldn't resist seeing these heavenly crystals together as one divine incarnation of dreaminess...

Sterling silver-plated brass wire and fittings, Swarovski crystal and crystal pearls.

name: red pearl text necklace
description:
A quirky take on the eighties from one who took it seriously!

A bold and sleek necklace which will sit back beautifully with all the bat-winged slouchy tops and jackets you can get your hands on.

The rare vintage Czech glass pearls and the 22ct shiny gold-plated German box-chain put together with matt black fittings makes this a necklace a little 'artier' than your run of the mill eighties style jewellery.

The red in the faux pearls is so beautiful, and not available in current costume pearls, believe me I have looked everywhere. The quality of the sheeny red is very special.

'to die for'

name: hoya leaf brooch
description:
An exceptionally delightful cartoon-like brooch which will bring smiles to people's faces, and yet has an intrinsic design/art quality.

The very dark green leaf, is almost black, except that the sparkling Swarovski crystal brings a splash light and fun to the piece.

Polymer clay, Swarovski crystal, stainless steel

name: cornucopia-of-feather brooch
description:
This is a wild and fabulous brooch which will make you smile.

The darkest green/black poly-clay cornucopia has tiny Swarovski lilac coloured crystal diamontés embedded in it and holds a lush bouquet of teal-coloured 'chinchilla' feathers. 

You will never see anything like this anywhere else either.

Too good to miss

name: swaying silver earrings
description:
The photographs here just don't do these beautiful ethereal earrings justice! 
Streams of pastel, silver and clear crystals pour down from a signature t-bar component to create these subtle yet sophisticated timeless earrings reminiscent of morning rain or a gentle waterfall...

Sterling silver-plated pewter and brass, Swarovski crystal

Sterling silver hook

11 cms long

name: wattlesque ring
description:
A wild-and-woollie cluster of glass 'petal' shaped beads are bound together on this stainless steel adjustable ring.

This is a fun ring which we don't advise doing wearing for practical wayfaring!

Czech glass, stainless steel

made-to-order, available in seven colours

name: chantoozie earrings
description:
These funky retro-style earrings are very light to wear as the beads are handmade almost like papier maché. 

I was given these beads by a very kind Czechoslovakian gentleman many years ago. He'd arrived in Australia with his small costume jewellery factory and was retired. He told me these were made of semolina and fish scales are what give the pearl-esque shine. You'd think they'd have gone off by now, but they were treated with some kind of preservative. He told me all beads of this sort at that time were made like this.

I've finally had the heart to use them in this little range I've called 'Chantoozie' after the most wonderful band who used to bring the house down.

The chain and hooks are 22ct gold-plated brass
length 9cms

name: chantoozie necklace
description:
An easy-to-wear Chartreuse coloured necklace which you just throw on to bring a note of savvy retro mod to your ensemble.

I was given these beads by a very kind Czechoslovakian gentleman many years ago. He'd arrived in Australia with his small costume jewellery  factory and was retired. He told me these were made of semolina and fish scales are what give the pearl-esque shine. You'd think they'd have gone off by now, but they were treated with some kind of preservative. He told me all beads of this sort at that time were made like this.

I've finally had the heart to use them in this little range I've called 'Chantoozie' after the most wonderful band who used to bring the house down.

The chain and findings are 22ct gold-plated brass

name: chantoozie bracelet
description:
Chunky statement, retro Chartreuse coloured beads from the sixties cluster together densely on 22ct gold-plated chain to make this deliciously wicked bracelet.

I was given these beads by a very kind Czechoslovakian gentleman many years ago. He'd arrived in Australia with his small costume jewellery production factory and was retired. He told me these were made of semolina and fish scales is what gives the pearlesque shine. You'd think they'd have gone off by now, but they were treated with some kind of preservative. He told me all beads of this sort at that time were made like this.

I've finally had the heart to use them in this little range I've called 'Chantoozie' after the most wonderful band who used to bring the house down.

The chain and findings are 22ct gold-plated brass

name: blue calypso neckpiece
description:
Vibrant coloured glass bead necklace has a feeling of Haight Ashbury in the early days when hippies wore apparel and jewellery to reflect their
sense of freedom and joyous delight in colour.

This necklace is definitely about freedom, the freedom to enjoy colours inspired by exotic birds and tropical fish.

All glass beads, Czech and Indian. 'black-pearl'-plated brass fittings

name: digitalis necklace
description:
Hip HOp and 'classic' meet on a dance floor of unexpected colour and texture with this baby.

A fusion of quality and funk, this necklace will update anything and anyone in moments...even people not wearing it, do a double-take.

I think these are vulcanized rubber-clad glass beads.

name: cilla 1 earrings
description:
Big fabulous 'Mod' earrings, inspired by the sixties and Cilla Black!

Like Cilla they have soul and style, and attract attention with their subtle presence, refined simplicity.

Big smooth Scandinavian style carved wood and a recycled glass bead 
'Black-pearl'-plated brass hooks

Length: 10 cms

name: wattlesque neckpiece
description:
Very chunky and sculptural, this neckpiece is full of vitality, and vibrant with colour.

It will definitely make a big statement in its beautiful natural Autumnal colours. You need to have strong energy to wear this piece, or it will wear you!

Indian and exclusive Czech glass beads, 'black-pearl'-plated brass chain and fittings

name: wattlesque bracelet
description:
This wild chunky and fabulous sculptural bracelet is a big statement piece. Even though the colours are quite earthy and natural, the shapes and textures are pretty amazing. The translucent orange pod-like glass beads mixed in with the opaque detailed leaf shapes is poetic.

A mixture of Indian and exclusive Czech glass beads and 'black-pearl'-plated brass.

name: storm-of-greens bracelet
description:
This wild and percussive bracelet is a delicious reminder of how in nature you'll see all kinds of shapes, colours and sizes of leaves together.

It has a tropical feeling to it.
The glass beads are vintage Indian, so better quality than one can generally get today.
They are wired onto 'black-pearl'-plated brass fittings and chains.

name: Mata Earrings
description:
Fabulous! Outrageous! Very large jet hoop earrings

Named after the infamous Mata Hari, the beautiful and seductive Dutch spy who won her way into men's hearts with her guile and magic.

Swarovski jet crystal hoops, with a large moulded glass bead out of which a mixed black chain tassel sensually sweeps your shoulders as you swan around in these show-stopper earrings (or head dress really)

Swarovski jet crystal, moulded glass, 'black-pearl'-plated brass chains and fittings

name: Palace ring
description:
Beautiful Candy Spender classic, the 'Palace' ring with its 'baguette'
shaped vintage Swarovski crystal stone set in handcast Sterling
silver.
The elegant Palace ring is a picture of elegant glamour and is in store currently.

They've been re-mastered by the talented Justin Boehm, so that the stone
now fits snuggly and beautifully into this classic setting, which was originally
inspired by a ring my mother used to wear from the forties.

The vintage Swarovski tourmaline crystal baguette stone is subtle and understated, a slightly earthy green, and looks exquisite with the silver, at the time of writing there are only 2 stones left. (Feb 2013)

They're just so timeless and elegant, and I've been producing them now for over twenty years. I'm starting to run out of the stones, which are vintage Swarovski crystal, so they're a limited edition.

Medium size

name: cocktail treasure ring
description:
Large round ring which is known to stop traffic!
Hand-cast Sterling silver (925), Swarovski crystal,
signed

This is a signature piece which I designed in 1990, and have recently had re-mastered.

People who own one (or two) of these tell me that they go on and on wearing them, and
the ring alway represents a particular state of mind, a feeling of empowerment and 
well-being. They look great on any of your fingers, although I like them best on the middle
finger.

There are five colours available, see pic.

Please contact us before ordering for size and stone availability

name: Laxmi ring
description:
Large 'tear drop' shaped ergonomic ring with 'filigree' detail.
Sterling silver (925), Swarovski crystal, signed and stamped.

This ring is a Candy Spender must-have classic if you're at all serious about collecting Candy Spender jewels. I have customers who have one in each colour!
The Gaudi-style filigree sides bring a delicacy to this exquisite ring. You can wear them all the time, they are ergonomically very comfortable, and sit back with anything from jeans to party dress.

Although we do carry some stock, you will need to enquire about sizes and availability
You won't regret it!

This has been one of the most popular items I've ever produced, and has been going since 1990. It has recently been re-mastered and is better than ever. I wear my jet/silver one everyday, and have been for the last twenty years. I like the scuffed looking crystal jet, and find the ring hardly interferes with my active lifestyle.

You can order it in one of four exquisite colours.

Please contact us before ordering

name: fire urchin cuff
description:
Fabuous colourful and fun 'urchin' cuff, a signature piece.

Hot colours, this incredible bracelet will make your heart skip a beat, it has already appeared in fjorde magazine and created a stir.

Vintage Czech glass, and cut glass beads on 'black-pearl'-plated brass fittings and chain.

Be quick, this is a one-off and the truth is, you really won't be able to get through summer without it.

name: Sienna storm bracelet
description:
Rich dark terracotta coloured glass 'pod' like beads in a cluster of gorgeousness. A Candy Spender signature piece.
Vintage Indian glass beads, Czech glass seed beads, 'black pearl' plated brass chain and findings.

This exquisite bracelet/cuff sienna coloured beads makes 
a lovely sound when you move your wrist, and creates a slightly mysterious sense of a contemporary yet ancient looking cuff.

The glass pod-like beads are each ended with a teal green
Czech glass seed bead, a beautiful little detail, which adds depth and quality to this beautiful bracelet.

name: Big Island Bracelet
description:
An unexpected combination of beautiful fine white agate, lime jade, plastic vintage costume pearls, Indian glass beads, and resin. Sterling silver toggle.

This unique chunky bracelet is a timeless piece you will have in your wardrobe forever!

This is one big fat bracelet, which really looks absolutely heaven on a tanned or dark wrist, with heavily pearl varnished nails. 
Worn with a rattan coloured top and white pants or sarong...delicious!!

was $350

name: Babylon Charm bracelet
description:
OTT!! This one-of-a-kind gold charm bracelet is truly incredible and amazing.
This over-the-top charm bracelet is a wicked and outrageous take on those huge bracelet people wore in the sixties. You need to mix this up with 
big plastic or resin bangles and a big fat watch, (which is too big for you...)

All the components excepting the feather (vintage) are Candy Spender's own castings from over twenty years ago, so they're really vintage Candy 
Spender!

The Swarovski crystal stones set in the leaf and 'earth cross', as well as the big round light topaz coloured one, which has its own beautiful setting gleam and sparkle as only Swarovski does.

22C gold-plated brass and pewter; Swarovski crystal; vintage beads and charms; glass; resin

name: Persephone hearts bracelet
description:
Exquisite and iconic. This bracelet is made up of vintage Candy Spender
components, the rich gold combined with dark blue and jet crystal is
very beautiful and special.

Nestled in beautiful brushed gold heart components are dark and mysteriously beautiful Swarovski crystal hearts. The dark blue (montana) is one of those elegant Swarovski colours that they call one of their classics, as it is always popular, it suits most people and never dates. But when you put it next to the rich 22ct gold-plated piece it sits in, your breath gets taken away! And when you combine it with
jet crystal, it makes it even more sophisticated and beautiful.

Vintage 22ct gold-plated pewter and brass, Swarovski crystal.

name: montana Persephone bracelet
description:
Vintage Swarovski marquise crystal stones in a rich arrangement, 
make this 'the thinking woman's' charm bracelet.

This is a beautiful edgy, yet feminine bracelet, which has a subtle 
charm bracelet sort of movement, and yet is quite structured and
orderly. The beautiful subtle colour of montana, a dark slate blue
classic Swarovski colour, set in 22ct gold and 'black-pearl' plated
pewter (from the archival Candy Spender component collection).

One-of-a-kind luxurious and beautiful, this stylish bracelet will
update your wardrobe, it is edgy and current, yet there is a stunning
timelessness about it as well.

was $390

name: Diamonds n Rust Cuff
description:
Very detailed cuff containing vintage Czech fire-polished glass beads, threaded throughout are tiny brass chains which create a sense of subtle movement. 

This is a significant and very detailed piece. At the front of this cuff is an 'Earth Star', a 'black pearl'-plated pewter four pointed star, with a Swarovski crystal set in the middle. The endings match the Earth Star, and have a slightly 'Goth' feel about them. They are all Candy Spender originals.

was $450

name: Ghana Gal neckpiece
description:
Magnificent fabulous and loud! This neckpiece is for the Amazon Goddess in you, it will set your heart on fire with its vibrant colours and textures.

An eclectic mixture of Tibetan, African and Indian beads, with the highlight given to us by line of smooth and refined Czech glass white beads.

The big fat orange recycled glass beads which inspired the neckpiece are from Ghana, and I've never seen such an alive orange as this in glass. They just take your breath away, and by the time you've caught your breath you'll just want to dance with this over your heart...

It is large and heavy and I don't recommend wearing it to your day job, as its will demand attention continuously and distract everyone from the task at hand. Its empowering and definitely not for the faint-hearted.

Glass, 'black-pearl'and 22k gold-plated brass chains and fittings.

name: King Lotus ll fringed necklace
description:
Exotic and detailed this necklace is tasseled lushness incarnate!

I have used many vintage Swarovski stones in my own settings to create this beautiful luxurious neckpiece. Its sensuality and delicious presence will transport you to many and varying realms. You will be able to wear it to the prom, or to your wedding, or toan important formal event. And also snap it on over a tank top and jeans, or your swimming suit for that matter. It is just one of those pieces that once you have it in your wardrobe you just will not be able to be without it. A powerful personal talisman and magical companion.

All Swarovski crystal beads and stones, some of them vintage from the oldest part of my collection (fifties!). The components are 22ct gold-plated pewter. The fine chains are German,
brass and also 22ct gold-plated.

This is definitely a one-of-a-kind moment in time that this piece is appearing in, and if you are serious about collecting fine original costume jewellery pieces, well this is definitely one for you.

name: Aphrodite lll necklace
description:
Large bold, shiny and colourful gold-plated asyymentric necklace of Swarovski crystal stones.

This is such a fabulous and unique statement piece! The rich colours of the gorgeous Swarovski crystal stones set in amongst the shiny gold chains and big bold components are deliciously lush and glamorous.

This necklace will sit beautifully with a simple elegant evening dress or gown, and the next morning you can just pull on your jeans and a brightly colourful neo-hippie top, gold sandals and go for a cruise into the yacht club for cocktails. It really is as versatile as that.


22ct gold-plated signature pewter components and 22ct gold-plated brass German box chain
and fittings.

A collectors piece and not for the faint-hearted!

name: tantric rainbow necklace
description:
Hippie-chic! This richly coloured necklace will make your heart beat faster.
The Swarovski crystal strands are heavenly, and the pendant is molded glass, with a foiled back. Beautiful colours.

This necklace is one of those sorts of accessories you will become addicted to, as it is not only beautiful, but a real 'feel good' piece as well.
Six strands of delciously rainbow coloured Swarovski crystals, with some surprising moments of size variation (where the rose pink is)...just to add a feeling of something natural.

One-of-a-kind

name: Wing Woman ll
description:
This is definitely a collectors item, it is one-of-a-kind, and has represented Candy Spender Jewels as a definitive signature piece for the last three years. Big colourful Swarovski stones (some of them vintage) are set in our own 22c brushed-gold-plated pewter cup casting, (big ones are signed). 

The heavy centre piece of the necklace sticks out a little from the neck, emphasising the large stones, and giving an effect of a stiffened collar.

This is a big necklace, and always the first thing people oooh and aaah at when they visit my showroom,
its a show stopper.

All Swarovski crystal, (some vintage), 22C gold-plated pewter and brass.

name: red chaos necklace
description:
Fabulous chunky three stranded necklace of deep and bright red cut glass.
This is one of our perenniel classics, the 'chaotic' series of necklaces.

It has a beautiful organic quality about it, as if it grew into those beautiful
juicy bright and dark red crystals. Everyone should have a strong red piece
of jewellery in their wardrobe for those days when you need a boost of energy and 'Shakti'. (life-force)

These never date, we have customers who tell us they still wear theirs, even though they bought it fifteen years ago!

The chunky red crystals are strung onto the most robust of the stringing materials, all black, with 'black-pearl'-plated German brass fittings. Just great quality, which will endure and endure, and give much wear for years and years.

NB: Please contact us before ordering as we do not always have the beads in supply

name: Wet Tar necklace
description:
Minimal black necklace of sparkling Swarovski crystal and Miyuki 
Japanese glass bugle beads.

This subtle piece has some surprising and exquisite details which
take people by surprise when they handle it.

To begin with, it has a beautiful sensual 'drape' for such a fine piece,
this is because of the quality of the stringing material and beads.

It is 'opera' length, and can easily be worn over a fine knit, or linen
top casually, or over silk or netting as a glamorous addition.

name: Jet shadows neckpiece
description:
An eighties inspired large long necklace with unexpected details of
jet and handcast black pewter components. Glamour and deep 
beauty.

This amazing long and chunky, yet very fine neckpiece is a reflection of the times, 
inspired by the broadshouldered slouchy eighties, and yet with a glamour and sensibility of Now, will undoubtedly become and Candy Spender collectors piece as it contains the signature components, a slightly Goth edge, but with an elegance and beauty which is timeless.

All Swarovski crystal (some vintage) and crystal black pearls. 'Black-pearl'-plated handcast pewter and fittings.

name: Sleek Persephone necklet
description:
All Swarovski crystal stones set into our own hand-cast pewter cup components, which have been either plated in a rich 22ct brushed-gold or a 'black-pearl' dark finish. They are linked up at the top so that they sit in a perky row around your neck, glimmering away. When people see this on, they have to do a double-take, because they're not sure whether there is an illusion of three dimensionality about the colour arrangement or not. (there is such a beautiful graduation of colours here)

It is a most flattering and beautiful necklet, which will happily live in your jewellery wardrobe for years. You know that whenever you wear it, a delicate sophisticated sensibility is conveyed.

name: Amour du Temps necklace
description:
Amazing dark red crystal heart in a dark leafy exclusive
vintage Candy Spender setting, on a three stranded vintage
Czech glass pearl necklace.

This is a unique and amazingly nostalgic piece which captures the mood
of our times, many people are holding their hearts as they release their
pasts, and their expectations, opening to a new way of loving and living.

I have used components from my archives, including the amazing Czech
glass pearls, which are the most beautiful subtle oyster cream colour, with a certain 'j'ne sais pas' feel about them. They're probably from the fifties.

The Swarovski siam crystal heart is something they don't make anymore
either. I created the setting especially for this stone, and this is the last 
siam one. There's something very poignant about that deep red, black
and oyster coloured pearl.

I have hung a small garnet Swarovski heart from the extension chain at
the back, to add more sensuality.

name: Czarina ll neckpiece
description:
This is an elaborate and complex piece which on the one hand seems to be very chaotic and organic, yet it has actually been constructed meticulously with great attention to detail and is very structured.

The base consists of beautiful Swarovski crystal stones set in 22ct gold-plated pewter cup settings, and wired Swarovski crystal beads. Threaded on one half of the choker are layers and layers of loops and 'stalks' all made from Swarovski crystal & crystal pearls, Japanese Delica, Czech glass and vintage gold glass beads. 

An 'alchemical' mélange of light and warm shades of gold and shimmering silver. This is a very rich and lush statement piece, ideal for a couture gown, or even to bring a simple silkslip right up into another genre, this is handcrafted Couture at its finest.

name: Coco pearls necklace
description:
Inspired by the great Coco Chanel and her layers of pearl 
necklaces, all of different sizes and types. Timeless style.

This is the third 'Coco pearls' layered necklace I've made. 
The last two were using Japanese costume pearls, this one
is very special as it is all Swarovski crystal pearls. The Swarovski
crystal pearls have an inner light, a radiance about them as
luminous as natural pearls, and yet they are much more robust.

The best quality costume pearls known.
was $790

This is a fabulous, ravishingly beautiful neckpiece, which you 
can wear equally as a formal piece as you can with jeans.

name: chunky chaos pearl necklace
description:
This beautiful textural crystal pearl necklace is shown here in a 'latté colour, which I always think is so flattering and subtle. The soft sheen of the Swarovski crystal pearls, and their seemingly random placement on this multi-stranded neckpiece has a timeless elegance about it, and can be worn in many different ways, for example quite formally with a wedding
dress, or just with a beautiful little tailored jacket for a chic sophisticated look. Or quite casually over fine knitwear, or with a silk blouse. It is one of those versatile pieces which will make you feel great everytime you wear it, as though the world is your oyster!

The Swarovski crystal pearls are so radiant and beautiful, one can't help comparing them to real pearls, yet they are far more robust than real pearls, as they remain unaffected by skin chemistry, perfume or hairspray. 

I have been making versions of these for over fifteen years, and they go on being one of my classics that people love.

Swarovski crystal pearls, sterling-silver fittings

name: Edwardianna Neckpiece
description:
Large and elaborate Edwardian inspired neckpiece of
Czech glass (some vintage), Swarovksi crystal and 22c 
gold-plated brass fittings.

The influence is from those elaborate Edwardian costumes and architectural elements which our great grand parents lived in. It was a time of innocence and yet deep culture.

The necklace is a take on that era, slightly tongue-in-cheek.

The sand-blasted dark cherry Czech beads which make up the necklace
side of things are subtle and beautiful, and sit back elegantly with the
pendant which has been hand-sculpted with poly-clay and is set with
one large multi-coloured vintage Czech glass cabochon stone, and 
crowned with a beautiful satin blue vintage Czech cabochon three
petal 'flower'. I have laid tiny seed Czech pearls around the oval stone,
and surrounded those with Swarovsksi crystal garnet stones.

was $650

name: Diamonds n Rust Choker
description:
This is an outstanding original and I'm told a 'work of art'. It is a beautifully crafted and durable piece which can be worn in a minimalist way, or 'layered' with other pieces to bring some serious depth to 
them, as shown in the editorial photograph here. (styled by Julia-Louise Premoselli)

The glass 'feathers' are a bit like an Abacus, and can be moved from side-to-side, giving a sort of natural feel to the piece.

Custom Czech glass 'feathers', vintage Czech fire polished glass and, Swarovski crystals. 'Black-pearl'-plated brass wire and findings.

Collectors item

was $1200

name: Peace Tassle
description:
The tassel is made out of a 1920's fringe from 
Candy's Antique and vintage collection.

Antique crystals, vintage Swarovski, 
iolite, fresh water pearls, and labradolite.

The wire is all 'black-pearl'-plated copper and brass.

was $850

name: Barkti Necklace
description:
Chunky elegant classic neckpiece.
Vintage pressed metal Indian beads, Swarovski crystal, 'black-pearl'-plated brass

An unusual and strong piece, looks fabulous with leather. 
It sits just at the base of the neck, but has an adjustment chain, so can be worn as a choker or a bit longer as a necklet.
Look very 'eighties' with neat tailored jacket.

Sculptural and cool.

name: Diamonds n Rust Fringe Necklace
description:
Big luscious one-of-a-kind neckpiece, which you can wear with your jeans or over a classic white linen kaftan, either way it will stop people in their tracks.

This summer with your bikini, on a fragrant terrace of scented flora, and the clinking of glasses as you delight in the warm summer breezes, or wrapped in a shawl of alpaca, the winter air and drizzle; either way, you will feel connected to the pulse of street life as well as Nature in all her glory. This is what this necklace evokes, because it is sophisticated earthy-ness.

All German copper chain and brass findings. The copper-ie coloured beads are vintage Czech fire-polished glass.
Hand-made sterling silver clasp.

was $620


model is Danielle Mullins, photographer Amy Stokes

name: blak resin layered necklace
description:
Double stranded and chunky matt and shiny black resin.
Fabulous black necklace, with some drama and presence.

The mix textures and matt and shiny layers of black resin and the way they've been place bring a decorative yet powerful ambient to this necklace.

Its great to wear with a tailored suit jacket or with a fifties style white cotton, summer dress. Either way it makes an important statement, and shows the world you are happy to show your feminine power in a sophisticated and self-confident way, while still keeping your feet on the ground.

was $220

name: Blak Petal Garland Necklace
description:
Delicate and beguiling garland of black rose petals strung onto waxed linen,has a contemporary minimal look, and is great as a 'layer' with other more chunky pieces.

poly-clay, waxed linen, each 'petal' is hand sculpted

name: blak chip necklace
description:
Black glossy resin 'chips' hand-knotted silk, necklace for
all occasions.

This is just one of those necklaces which will get worn and worn, it sits back in a most chilled and relaxed way with everything from a tailored suit, to an asymmetric knitted dress, to a shirt with jeans. Its just an simple easy piece, and is great for layering with other necklaces which need more depth.

Smooth 'black-pearl'-plated brass parrot clasp and fittings.

The hand-knotted silk shows that its been thought about, and brings a sense of quality.

name: Wilma quartz necklace
description:
These are beautiful graduated huge light-filled quartz beads, just fantastic!! Polished quartz crystal beads, will sit around your neck rather like Wilma Flintstone's necklace.

Big sculptural piece, with large sterling silver clasp, for easy on-and-off.

I don't think these will last, I've made three. Small, Medium & large.

Be quick!

name: Cobalt Resin Ladder Necklace
description:
The blue in this necklace is the thing! It is an absolutely incredible deep cobalt blue, and the photograph really doesn't do it justice, as it has a translucence about it hard to capture.

Suffice it to say that it will bring life to many other colours, and will look equally gorgeous on cream and pastels, as it will on one solid strong colour like dark green or tangelo orange.

Sale was $160

name: Harlequin 1 earrings
description:
Fabulous highly colourful Swarovski crystals and 22ct brushed gold-plated chain-mail style marquise shaped earrings.

These earrings swing with you, as your energy quickens wearing them!
Like chain-mail they follow the surface they're on, and they hang softly,
moving with your body organically.

The colours are surprisingly rich and deep, yet have a playful quality.
Length is 10 cms, big earrings with a big heart.

name: Harlequin 3 earrings
description:
Fabulous highly colourful Swarovski crystals and 22ct brushed gold-plated chain-mail style marquise shaped earrings.

These earrings swing with you, as your energy quickens wearing them!
Like chain-mail they follow the surface they're on, and they hang softly,
moving with your body organically.

The colours are energetic and playful, the density of opaque crystal.
Length is 10 cms, big earrings to bring big smiles.
was $360

name: Aphrodite ll earrings
description:
Juicy Lucy!! 
These earrings are full of life and colour, they're
a big lush colourful joyous statement in Swarovski crystal and
brushed gold.

All Swarovski crystal set in 22ct gold-plated pewter and brass,
these earrings will put a smile on your face and everyone who
sees you wearing them, the bright saturated colours work together
in an extraordinary alchemy of Joy and fun.
The brushed rich gold turns them into luxury.

name: lilac froth n foam earrings
description:
Exquisite and joyful earrings, these shining beauties are a feminine statement with their flattering radiant pastel crystals and the palest of pink pearls.

All Swarovski crystal and crystal pearls set in 22ct gold-plated pewter
hand cast cups and brass fittings.

These earrings bring a smile to people's faces, they are so beautiful and
so filled with light.

They also have their own stylish couture presence and look equally 
divine with your little black cocktail dress as they do with your wedding
gown.

name: 'flowers'1 earrings
description:
Swarovski crystals wired together in the form of flowers, to create these
earrings in a celebration of joyous colour!

Hand-wired flower earrings are absolutely heaven! Especially if you are 
a lover of strong saturated colours, and crystals. 

These earrings are guaranteedto lift the mood of any place you walk into wearing them, that's because when you spot yourself in the mirror a big smile will burst onto your face, and as you
know smiling is contagious!

You can wear them casually for a day-time gathering or event, as well as take them into the evening, the crystals sparkle like champagne.

Swarovski crystal, enameled copper wire, 22ct gold-plated brass fittings.

9 cms long

name: 'flowers' 2 earrings
description:
Two hand-wired Swarovski crystal flowers subtle yet colourful
disceetly compelling and beautiful.

These hand-wired flower earrings are naturally beautiful! Especially if you are a lover of natural quite earthy colours, and crystals! These earrings ooze feminine elegance and charm, they make a statement in a laid-back natural way.

You can wear them casually for a day-time gathering or event, as well as take them into the evening, the crystals sparkle like champagne.

Swarovski crystal, enameled copper wire, 22ct gold-plated brass fittings.

5cms long

name: 'flowers' 4 earrings
description:
Subtle Swarovski crystal flower earrings, beautiful rich earthy colours.

These hand-wired flower earrings are naturally beautiful.  The colours in these earrings are like a beautiful bouquet of autumnal flowers in the afternoon light.

These earrings just ooze feminine elegance and charm, and make a statement in a subtle natural way.

You can wear them casually for a day-time gathering or event, as well as take them into the evening, the crystals sparkle like champagne.

Swarovski crystal, enameled copper wire, 22ct gold-plated brass fittings.

8.5 cms long

name: 'flowers' 3 earrings
description:
Sweet and elegant, all Swarovski crystal flowers with stone components, 
these beautiful earrings have a nostalgic feel and delicacy..

Hand-wired flower earrings are exquisite! Especially if you are 
a lover of delicate feminine colours, and crystals. Grounding the ephemeral crystal work, are the stones set in our own cup settings.

These earrings are guaranteed to lift the mood of any place you walk into wearing them, that's because whenyou spot yourself in the mirror a delicious smile will slide across your face, and as you
know smiling is contagious!

Swarovski crystal beads and stones, gold-plated copper wire, 22ct brushed gold-plated pewter components
and fittings.

Swarovski crystal, enameled copper wire, 22ct gold-plated brass fittings.

10 cms long

name: fire hoops
description:
These large vivacious double hooped earrings will start a party 
where ever they are worn, they just ooze fun and delight!

Czech glass, including custom 'feather' (aka 'dagger') beads.
A beautiful and extroverted combination of reds, from vermillion
to brick. They will sit back beautifully with your swimmers or
your exotic sarong, and even your 'little-black-dress'. They are
the perfect holiday earrings. (whether you're on holiday or not,
they are a holiday from the mundane!)

handmade stering silver hooks

name: Garden earrings
description:
Colourful and juicy double hooped earrings with delicate vintage brass leaf charm.

These spicy double hooped earrings will add a smile and a happy note to your day. 
The beads are a mixture of Czech glass and Japanese Delica glass, so beautiful saturated colours, and some of them are double colours.
There is such a diverse variety of colour the earrings will sit back beautifully with any colour or colour group you wish to put them with.

The tiny vintage pressed brass leaf adds a delicate touch, and slightly Gypsy feel.

The hooks are hand made sterling silver.

name: black onyx lily earrings
description:
These Art Nouveau style earrings are so lusciously elegant and have an old world charm about them, yet an contemporary edge which makes them unique and hard to define.

Hand-carved black onyx, Swarovski Black crystal pearl and crystal, Czech glass, 'black-pearl-plated' brass wire hand made hooks

They measure 7.5 cms long

name: Black lilies turmaline earrings
description:
These really are such beautiful earrings. The Swarovski crystal stones
set in matt 'black-pearl'-plated cup settings are so deeply rich and lustrous.

The Swarovski stones are vintage. And like all good vintage, there is a 
certain quality of depth and chic which can't be reproduced.

There were two pairs, this is that last one.

7cms long

name: Black Leaf earrings
description:
Contemporary and minimal, like floating leaves these earrings are so simple and easy to wear, they are light as a feather!

Poly-clay, 'black pearl'-plated brass.

Pictures shows 8cms long  (is available longer or shorter, you can specify that when you order.)

these are made-to-order and you can specify a length.
Allow 5-7 days.

name: montana Persephone earrings ll
description:
Elegant and 'lady-like' these timeless brushed gold
earrings take any occassion onto another level of 
style.

The dark blue vintage 'Montana' Swarovski crystal stones set
in 22ct brushed gold-plated pewter cup settings linked together
in a sublime and cool chic.

The larger round stone at the bottom has a lace-like black pattern,
embedded in it, and were a limited edition at Swarovski around 15 
years ago. 

Length 5.7 cms

(on SALE were $250)

name: Montana Persephone earrings
description:
Large marquise montana crystal set in 22ct gold-plated custom
setting dangles elegantly. These earrings are classic chic.

The large vintage Swarovski montana crystal is so beautiful set
against the rich gold, a timeless classic. The smaller stones in
their settings bring a finesse and beauty to this classic earring
which can be worn with your YSL tux or a satin evening or ball 
gown, as well as casually with your tailored work suit, to lift it
into another realm and impress, those who you want to show 
your savvy style off to.

Limited edition

name: 'Persephone hearts' earrings
description:
These are such beautiful and subtle earrings, and yet the warmth
of the gold and dark blue & jet crystal is vibrant and lush.

22ct brushed gold-plated pewter & brass. (nickle free)

Limited edition

name: Sahara Tassles
description:
Vintage Swarovski crystal stones. 22c gold-plated 
hand-cast pewter settings and German brass chain, 
and hooks.

These one-of-a-kind tassel earrings are exotic and absolutely unique.

The warmth of the gold next to the amber coloured crystal stones creates 
a luminous glow next to the skin. They are definitely not for the faint-hearted either!

They measure 13 cms long.

On SALE, were $410

name: Diamond Dog Earrings
description:
Inspired by David Bowie's 70's song 'Diamond Dogs'. 

Diamonte clip-on components are from the fifties, although sometimes I wonder whether they're earlier, because I can see Rita Hayworth or someone like that wearing them. They are very good quality 
costume jewellery, and I was lucky enough to find a bag of them on my travels fifteen years ago. 

They inspired these earrings, which will not date, they are so amazing.
This second version is slightly lighter than the original version I created several years ago. (more user friendly)

At the time of writing, there are only one pair left. (feb 2013)

They measure 11 cms.

vintage components: diamante top, Czech glass oyster pearl cabochons, Swarovski crystals, 'black pearl'-plated pewter 'cups', brass, stainless steel.

name: Hina Couture Earrings
description:
All vintage large pearl drops (some of them a little worn by their years!). 
Large clear Swarovski crystal stone set in our signature sterling silver-plated pewter cup settings, and all Swarovksi crystal and crystal pearls, 
on the 'stem' of these glorious creatures.

'Hina' is the Polynesian virgin Goddess, creatress of the world, and closely associated to the moon. 
Apparently all women embody her spirit! These earrings are definitely of the 'Goddess' realms.
(not for the faint hearted!)

They have been a stylists and photographers favorite over the years, and have an 'energy' about them which still bestows the wearer with amazing beauty, and elegance.

They measure 12.5 cms

On SALE, were $294

name: blak lilies 2 earrings
description:
Gold & black chic. These exquisite earrings are timeless in their
understated glamour and sophistication.

These stylish earrings are surprising and beautiful.

The dark 'black-pearl'-plated pewter in contrast to the gorgeous
22 ct brushed gold-plated pewter components together create 
a depth and subtle intensity for the beautiful glimmering Swarovski crystal stones to be framed by.

Perfectly balanced, these earrings look amazing on most people.

name: Emblem of Wave brooch
description:
A sparkling blue wave of a brooch

Swarovski crystal set in a simple wave shape of polymer clay.

This sharp brooch in sparkling blues is beautiful in it simplicity.
The work is intricate and detailed yet delivers something very
minimal.

Stainless steel swivel brooch pin

name: Emblem of Twist brooch
description:
Like sugar cane, this sweetly pinks-and-reds crystal encrusted brooch, is girly but with a twist!

Swarovski (some vintage) crystal, poly-clay, stainless steel swivel pin

one-of-a-kind

name: Emblem of Vintage brooch
description:
This is a slightly ironic take on a classic vintage brooch. 
The kind that would sit neatly on the collar of your aunt's favourite tailored jacket.

The large apricot coloured cabochon which nestles in the middle of the 
marquise crystal jet and 'black diamond' diamante's is from the twenties, 
rescued from another brooch, and has a slightly stressed 'foil', which 
gives it that soulful vintage appeal. 
All the stones are set on polyclay, and back with a strong stainless-steel brooch pin.

Vintage frosted Czech cabochon glass stone, vintage Swarovski crystal, poly-clay, stainless-steel

was $250
